attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

cards.name: Aerodactyl V
cards.text: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Rock Crush
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.name: Aerodactyl VSTAR
cards.text: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Lost Dive
attacks.text: Put the top 3 cards of your deck in the Lost Zone.

attacks.name: Ancient Star
attacks.text: Until this Pokémon leaves play, it gains an Ability that has the effect "Your opponent's Pokémon V in play, except any Aerodactyl VSTAR, have no Abilities." (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

cards.name: Sudowoodo
cards.text: Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo's extreme aversion to water merits special note.

attacks.name: Joust
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Impound
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

cards.name: Gligar
cards.text: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

attacks.name: Cyclone Pincers
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

cards.name: Gliscor
cards.text: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey... Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

attacks.name: Hurricane Shock
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.name: Makuhita
cards.text: There's a rumor of a traditional recipe for stew that Trainers can use to raise strong Makuhita.

attacks.name: Fake Out
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.name: Hariyama
cards.text: Hariyama that are big and fat aren't necessarily strong. There are some small ones that move nimbly and use moves skillfully.

attacks.name: Shove
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Muscular Slap
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

cards.name: Meditite
cards.text: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

attacks.name: Focus Fist
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

cards.name: Medicham
cards.text: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

attacks.name: Battle Step
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Fighting Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.name: Relicanth
cards.text: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokémon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.

attacks.name: Into the Deep
attacks.text: Put up to 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.

cards.name: Gastrodon
cards.text: Its search for food sometimes leads it onto land, where it leaves behind a sticky trail of slime as it passes through.

attacks.name: Recover
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon and heal all damage from it.

attacks.name: Earthquake
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.name: Mienfoo
cards.text: In one minute, a well-trained Mienfoo can chop with its arms more than 100 times.

cards.name: Mienshao
cards.text: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

attacks.name: Double Smash
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.

cards.name: Landorus
cards.text: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

attacks.name: Smashing Edge
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

cards.name: Binacle
cards.text: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

cards.name: Barbaracle

abilities.name: Lost Block
abilities.text: Your opponent puts any Prize cards they would take in the Lost Zone instead of into their hand.

cards.text: Seven Binacle come together to form one Barbaracle. The Binacle that serves as the head gives orders to those serving as the limbs.

cards.name: Carbink
cards.text: When beset by attackers, Carbink wipes them all out by firing high-energy beams from the gems embedded in its body.

attacks.name: Lucky Find
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Item cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.name: Rockruff
cards.text: This Pokémon can bond very strongly with its Trainer, but it also has a habit of biting. Raising a Rockruff for a long time can be challenging.

attacks.name: Double Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

cards.name: Falinks
cards.text: Five of them are troopers, and one is the brass. The brass's orders are absolute.

attacks.name: Fighting Headbutt
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness. If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V, this attack does 50 more damage.

cards.name: Stonjourner
cards.text: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokémon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.

attacks.name: Power Stone
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Fighting Energy cards from your hand to your Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Lost Shot
attacks.text: Put the top card of your opponent's deck in the Lost Zone.

cards.name: Spinarak
cards.text: Although the poison from its fangs isn't that strong, it's potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

attacks.name: Poison Sting
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.name: Ariados
cards.text: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.

attacks.name: String Bind
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Venomous Fang
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.name: Murkrow
cards.text: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow's presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.

cards.name: Honchkrow
cards.text: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.

attacks.name: Night Cyclone
attacks.text: Move all Energy from this Pokémon to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

cards.name: Seviper
cards.text: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.

attacks.name: Sucker Punch and Turn
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Darkness Pokémon.

cards.name: Spiritomb

abilities.name: Cursed Message
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.text: Exactly 108 spirits gathered to become this Pokémon. Apparently there are some ill-natured spirits in the mix.

attacks.name: Chain of Spirits
attacks.text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Spiritomb in your discard pile.

cards.name: Drapion V

abilities.name: Wild Style
abilities.text: This Pokémon's attacks cost Colorless less for each of your opponent's Single Strike, Rapid Strike, and Fusion Strike Pokémon in play.

cards.text: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dynamic Tail
attacks.text: This attack also does 60 damage to 1 of your Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

abilities.text: During your turn, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Paralyzed and Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 3 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

cards.text: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Big Bang Arm
attacks.text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

cards.name: Darkrai
cards.text: On a moonless night, a strange incident occurred in which every one of a village's inhabitants suffered nightmares. The villagers attested that Darkrai appeared before them in these nightmares.

attacks.name: Nightmare
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Pitch-Black Blade
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

cards.name: Inkay
cards.text: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.name: Hoopa
cards.text: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

attacks.name: Hand of Djinn
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Darkness Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

cards.name: Radiant Hisuian Sneasler

abilities.name: Poison Peak
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, put 2 more damage counters on your opponent's Poisoned Pokémon.

cards.text: Because of Sneasler's virulent poison and daunting physical prowess, no other species could hope to best it on the frozen highlands. Preferring solitude, this species does not form packs.

attacks.name: Poison Jab
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

cards.name: Radiant Steelix
cards.text: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

cards.name: Bronzor
cards.text: It appears in ancient ruins. The pattern on its body doesn't come from any culture in the Galar region, so it remains shrouded in mystery.

cards.name: Bronzong
cards.text: Some believe that its bell-like cry opens holes to another world. It has been revered as a deity since ancient times.

attacks.name: Gravitational Drop
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

cards.name: Galarian Stunfisk
cards.text: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.

attacks.name: Field Trap
attacks.text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it. If you discarded a Stadium in this way, discard 2 Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

cards.name: Magearna
cards.text: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

attacks.name: Windup Beam
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has a Pokémon Tool attached, this attack does 60 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

cards.name: Galarian Perrserker V
cards.text: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

cards.name: Goomy
cards.text: Goomy hides away in the shade of trees, where it's nice and humid. If the slime coating its body dries out, the Pokémon instantly becomes lethargic.

cards.name: Hisuian Sliggoo
cards.text: A creature given to melancholy. I suspect its metallic shell developed as a result of the mucus on its skin reacting with the iron in Hisui's water.

attacks.name: Rigidify
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 50 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

cards.name: Hisuian Goodra

abilities.name: Metal Lodging
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to each of your Basic Pokémon that has any Metal Energy attached by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon V.

cards.text: Able to freely control the hardness of its metallic shell. It loathes solitude and is extremely clingy—it will fume and run riot if those dearest to it ever leave its side.

cards.name: Hisuian Goodra V
cards.text: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Slip-'n'-Trip
attacks.text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rolling Shell
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

cards.name: Hisuian Goodra VSTAR

abilities.name: Moisture Star
abilities.text: During your turn, you may heal all damage from this Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

cards.text: VSTAR rule: When your Pokémon VSTAR is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Rolling Iron
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 80 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

cards.name: Pidgeot V

abilities.name: Vanishing Wings
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may shuffle it and all attached cards into your deck.

cards.text: V rule: When your Pokémon V is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Flight Surf
attacks.text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 80 more damage.

cards.name: Lickitung
cards.text: If this Pokémon's sticky saliva gets on you and you don't clean it off, an intense itch will set in. The itch won't go away, either.

cards.name: Lickilicky
cards.text: Lickilicky's strange tongue can stretch to many times the length of its body. No one has figured out how Lickilicky's tongue can stretch so far.

cards.name: Porygon
cards.text: State-of-the-art technology was used to create Porygon. It was the first artificial Pokémon to be created via computer programming.

attacks.name: Branch Calculation
attacks.text: Look at the top 4 cards of either player's deck and put them back in any order.

cards.name: Porygon2
cards.text: This is a Porygon that was updated with special data. Porygon2 develops itself by learning about many different subjects all on its own.

attacks.name: Garbage Attack
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Pokémon Tool card in the Lost Zone (both yours and your opponent's).

cards.name: Porygon-Z
cards.text: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z's behavior.

attacks.name: Downgrading Beam
attacks.text: Devolve 1 of your opponent's evolved Pokémon by removing any number of Evolution cards from it. Your opponent shuffles those cards into their deck.

cards.name: Snorlax

abilities.name: Unfazed Fat
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon. (Damage is not an effect.)

cards.text: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

attacks.name: Thumping Snore
attacks.text: This Pokémon is now Asleep. During Pokémon Checkup, flip 2 coins instead of 1. If either of them is tails, this Pokémon is still Asleep.

cards.name: Aipom
cards.text: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.

attacks.name: Mischievous Tail
attacks.text: Look at the top card of your opponent's deck. You may have your opponent shuffle their deck.

cards.name: Ambipom
cards.text: It uses its tails for everything. If it wraps both of its tails around you and gives you a squeeze, that's proof it really likes you.

attacks.name: All-You-Can-Grab
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. Search your deck for a number of cards up to the number of heads and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Knock Off
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

cards.text: These Pokémon can crush a car with no more than a headbutt. Bouffalant with more hair on their heads hold higher positions within the herd.

attacks.name: Lost Headbutt

abilities.name: All Just a Dream
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is Asleep and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.

attacks.name: Collapse

cards.name: Fantina

(This includes Pokémon that come into play during that turn.),You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

cards.text: Each player can't have more than 4 Benched Pokémon. If a player has 5 or more Benched Pokémon, they discard Benched Pokémon until they have 4 Pokémon on the Bench. The player who played this card discards first. If more than one effect changes the number of Benched Pokémon allowed, use the smaller number.
